# NestJS Project Standards

## Modular Design

- Every feature gets its own NestJS module: `src/<feature>/` containing `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.repository.ts`, `*.dto.ts`, `*.entity.ts`.
- Shared utilities, decorators, pipes, and guards go in `src/common/`.
- Modules must declare explicit exports — never rely on global scope leaking.

## Layered Architecture

- **Controllers**: request handling, input parsing, response shaping only.
- **Services**: all business logic lives here.
- **Repositories**: all persistence/DB interactions isolated here.
- Never call repositories from controllers or place HTTP logic in services.

## Naming & Structure Conventions

```
src/
  common/          # Shared pipes, guards, interceptors, decorators, filters
  config/          # Centralized configuration files
  <feature>/
    <feature>.module.ts
    <feature>.controller.ts
    <feature>.controller.spec.ts
    <feature>.service.ts
    <feature>.service.spec.ts
    <feature>.repository.ts
    dto/
      create-<feature>.dto.ts
      update-<feature>.dto.ts
    entities/
      <feature>.entity.ts
test/                        # E2e tests only
  <feature>.e2e-spec.ts
```

Use DTOs for **all** request/response validation — never pass raw bodies through.

## Configuration

- Centralize all config in `src/config/` and load via `@nestjs/config` (`ConfigModule`/`ConfigService`).
- All secrets and environment-specific values come from `.env` — never hardcode them.

## Error Handling & Logging

- Register a global exception filter (`APP_FILTER`) for consistent error responses.
- Use structured logging (`nestjs-pino` or equivalent) with levels: `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error`.
- Never swallow exceptions silently — always log before re-throwing or transforming.

## Testing

- Every service must have a colocated unit test file (`<name>.service.spec.ts`) next to the source.
- E2e tests for controllers live in `test/` as `<feature>.e2e-spec.ts`.
- Use `@nestjs/testing` `Test.createTestingModule` for test setup.

## API Documentation

- Annotate all endpoints and DTOs with `@nestjs/swagger` decorators (`@ApiTags`, `@ApiOperation`, `@ApiResponse`, `@ApiProperty`).
- Keep the OpenAPI spec in sync — update decorators whenever endpoints change.

## Security & Performance

- Validate all input with `class-validator` + `class-transformer` via `ValidationPipe` (global).
- Apply guards (`@UseGuards`) for authentication and role-based authorization.
- Use caching (`@nestjs/cache-manager`) and queues (`@nestjs/bull`) for heavy workloads.

## Repository Hygiene

- Enforce ESLint + Prettier on all commits.
- CI must pass lint + all tests before merge.
- Keep `main` branch deployable at all times.
